section.para:
During the JPA conversion it is a good opportunity to remove any code that is not
        necessary due to enhancements  in the core data fetching layer in the KRAD Data Module. The
        following are the best practices that should be used   when using JPA in Kuali applications.
        In general the order of consideration for a query should go as the following:


Use DataObjectService methods in service methods.



Create custom DAOs method to use NamedQuery in JPA.



Use Rice Criteria API if query is too complicated and would require dynamic
              generation(String concatenation).



Use JPA Criteria API if query requires functions not supported in Rice Criteria
              API.

